The forces of the giant strike are gathering
The League Unions and the National Federation of Workers’ Commissions will on Friday constitute a strike commission to coordinate Monday’s strike that will last indefinitely.
A protest rally will be held on Saturday, while on Monday - the day on which the final vote on the public health law will be held - work stoppage will begin.
Certainly this action will cause great difficulties in transport, since the railway transit will be stopped completely and until 13 hours the workers of the Budapest Collective Transport Company will also be on strike.
On Friday afternoon, the League Trade Unions will report on the details of their strike on Monday, which they will hold jointly with the National Federation of Workers’ Commissions.
The strike commission of the LIGA and the National Union of Machinists will also be set up to coordinate Monday’s actions.
A protest rally will be held on Saturday, while on Monday the participating unions will strike indefinitely if no agreement is reached with the government.
This means that - on the day of the parliamentary vote on the public health law - they did not report on the date of the end of the strike initiated.
If the National Assembly disapproves of the public health law, the unions will immediately withdraw their call to strike.
Instead, if the law is passed, the strike committees will meet and decide on the future.
On the basis of the National Assembly’s Monday agenda, it is also possible to vote only on the public health law in the very late hours of the night, or perhaps near midnight.
As a result of the strike that will start on Monday, there will be significant difficulties in transport: in the railways will stop working indefinitely, in the morning it may stop part of the collective transport of Budapest and more than half of the intercity transport of buses of the companies Vol<0xC3><0xA1>n.
At the same time, in many parts of the country, half of the roads will be closed.
Numerous trade unions and civil organizations have joined the strike, their names are constantly updated on the League’s website.
Some unions announced their strike indefinitely, others for a definite time.
Until Thursday afternoon, the State Railway and the Free Union of Railway Workers (SLTF) could not reach an agreement even on minimum services, although, as the Christmas holidays approach, more and more people travel on trains.
According to information received so far, from the beginning of the day until 1 pm workers of the Budapest Collective Transport Company will be on strike, the Budapest Airports from 7 am to 9 am, will hold a four-hour strike the LIGA unions of the electrical industry and thermal energy, the unions of the Educators called a strike of 2 and the union of Democtic 2.
The Hungarian Association of Physicians will strike nationally at alternative times and the Democratic Union of Health and Social Workers (SDTSSS) which is part of the Trade Union Cooperation Forum will hold a two-hour warning strike.
The most important of the four demands made by the League is that the government withdraw its proposal for public health reform and subject a new conception to a social debate.
The second demand is that they gradually introduce the new form of pension calculation that will come into effect next year.
The third is to ensure, even before 2010, that advanced pensions allow the occupations that deserve them to enter the system.
The fourth reason for the strike is that the Free Trade Union of Railway Workers (SLTF), which is part of the League Trade Unions, does not accept the proposal of the Ministry of Economy and Transport on the lateral railway lines and expect another different proposal.
Political Capital[b1]: In the country the risk is increased by the Hungarian Guard
According to the Risk Analysis Division of the Political Capital, the activity of the Hungarian Guard, formed in August this year with the support of the Movement for a Better Hungary, has increased the political risk of Hungary and the region from various points of view.
In the company's "risk warning" it is written: in relation to the activity of the Hungarian Guard the greatest political risk is the fact that "with the aggravation of ethnic tensions between the Roma and non-Gypsy population of Hungary, even in the short term violent ethnic clashes can occur".
The main reason for this is that the political strategy of the Hungarian Guard is probably the provocation of an event of this character - added the representative of the research institute.
They stated that all this is due to one of the main faults of the protagonists of Hungarian political life: "the protagonists of public life ceded the public debate of the Roma problem to the representatives of radical and extremist political groups, who were able to base their political strategy on the existing discrepancies between Roma and Hungarians".
This aggravates the problem, makes normal dialogue impossible, strengthens extremists, and increases the likelihood of violent conflict - they estimate.
In addition, according to the research institute, the activity of the National Guard, as a result of the great attention of the national and international media, "significantly deteriorated the image of Hungary abroad, especially in terms of stability and democratic development of the country".
We are reminded that: from the autumn of 2006 onwards, the reorganization of the radical and far-right groups in Hungary received increasing publicity and momentum and that since the summer of 2007 numerous organizations have been formed in the country that call themselves "national self-defense associations".
