Six hundred thousand drivers missed the date and therefore did not manage to change their old driver’s license whose validity ends at the end of the year.
Today is the last day when people can request the change so that officials will give them time until the end of the year to issue the new card.
However, the Ministry does not fear that after the New Year hundreds of thousands of drivers will be found on the roads without a valid license.
According to traffic, the card has not been changed mainly by those who no longer even want to drive.
While in the villages they announce a rapid decline in the change of cards, the offices of the metropolis are full of applications and interest in the new card has increased.
The City Council estimates about 2,000 customers daily.
In the queues you wait for half an hour.
Around 140,000 drivers have not yet been issued in Prague.
The issuance of a new card lasts 20 days.
However, it is possible to request the issuance of the card in a shorter period of five days.
But in that case the driver must pay five hundred crowns.
Drivers who must change their driving license and do not reach until the end of the year, but will go on the roads without the valid license will risk a fine from January.
The offender will pay a maximum of two thousand crowns.
The police can fix the offense with a warning.
In the event of an administrative violation, the fine will amount to 2,500 crowns.
According to the above information, a fine could be imposed on a person who does not go anywhere.
