The Congress approves the transposition of the Mifid, which entered into force November 1
Parallel to its parliamentary procedure, which ended today with the vote by Congress on the amendments incorporated into the bill in the Senate, the Government has submitted to public hearing the regulation that will develop the new law, with the aim that both enter into force before the end of the year.
The representatives of the different groups agreed to highlight the effort made by deputies and senators to negotiate and consensualize the best regulations in order to guarantee the protection of investors and regulate in detail the activity of the entities so that the markets function efficiently.
The MIFID, which amends the Securities Market Act, involves the modernisation of financial markets, while strengthening investor protection, improving the supervisory powers of the National Securities Market Commission (CNMV) and fostering cooperation between the various supervisors of the European Union.
The new rules will allow the provision of financial advisory services to specialised firms as well as to natural or legal persons and creates a new type of financial services firms (ESIS), financial advisory companies (AFIs), which join securities companies, securities agencies and portfolio management companies.
In addition, it expands the number of systems for the execution of transactions in financial instruments, so that regulated secondary markets are added to multilateral trading systems and order internalization systems, which will compete with current exchange managers.
The law also obliges investment firms to disclose information on the market about key aspects of their business profile, risk exposure and forms of risk management and requires them to keep a record of all the operations they perform, to facilitate supervision by the CNMV.
In his visit to the Congressional Economic Commission, several modifications were incorporated, among which he emphasizes that the securitized debts are considered as a "complex" financial instrument given their high danger to the investor, which has been demonstrated by what happened with the debt of high-risk U.S. mortgages (subprime).
In addition, the transposition of the directive was used to legally delimit the functions that graduates in Economics and Business can develop 30 years after the Royal Decree delimiting the professional functions reserved for economists was approved in 1977.
For its part, the Senate incorporated the creation of new figures in the financial sector, such as the mediator, who will work for an employee, will not require the authorization of the CNMV and will be able to provide its services of marketing products and attracting customers to different investment companies at the same time.
