Which insurance is right for me?
Car insurance, which covers the driver in case of possible accidents, is a significant expense that will depend on various factors, such as age, sex, age of the card, marital status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use of it, among others.
Having a car is just the beginning.
Choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing the vehicle model.
First of all, we must be clear about what we are talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insured.
This commitment is embodied in an insurance contract, which states that the company receives the value of the agreed premium in exchange for being responsible for the obligation to pay compensation in the event of a claim.
The premium is the price of the insurance, which is established taking into account various factors, such as age, sex, age of the card, marital status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use given to it, among others.
Insurance companies set their prices on the basis of statistics, so that the more likely you are to suffer an accident, the higher the fee to pay.
It is for this reason that both those over the age of 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, as statistics reflect that they have a lower accident rate due to their prudence.
Using counts, companies have concluded that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use that is given to the vehicle will influence the frequency, and with it the probability of having some type of mishap.
As the frequency increases, the odds increase.
There are many variables that insurers take into account when setting the premium price.
That is why the driver has to study the situation well to choose the car insurance that best suits his profile.
We will explain here the most significant variables when choosing one or another type of insurance, so that this, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insured, offers a reasonable price.
Young people under the age of 25 face various inconveniences when it comes to taking out insurance at an affordable price, such as reduced driving experience and the age of the driver’s license.
Although the ideal to be well insured is an all-risk insurance, there are other cheaper options.
The most cautious drivers can opt for an all-risk with franchise, so that they get insurance coverage at all-risk but at a more feasible price.
This kind of agreement would mean that the client would pay a portion of the amount of the claim.
"The part of the amount of the claim that the customer contributes will be pre-established according to the value of the premium, which will be higher the lower the amount", specifies Luis Noguera, head in Spain of First Europe, online insurance broker.
Another option is extended third-party insurance, so that the customer is assured protection against damage caused to third parties, although not to those caused in his own car.
In addition, it would be covered for theft, fire and loss of the vehicle.
One piece of advice.
If you are under 25 try to be careful and avoid claims as much as possible, as this will affect the bonus, which can reduce the cost of insurance in the future.
A bonus is a reduction on the base rate that the company owns.
On the contrary, a penalty is a surcharge on that base rate.
"The bonuses and penalties will depend on the company and the benefit of it.
If the company has had a good year it will be able to afford to increase the bonuses," explains Noguera.
After the age of 25, drivers have it easier when it comes to contracting insurance, since the accident rate is reduced thanks to the accumulated experience.
For this reason, it is most advisable to hire an all-risk franchise.
"Normally young people can not make use of the experience previously acquired when jumping in an accident, and even when driving," says the director in Spain of the European company, to which he adds that most accidents occur in the second year of driving, once passed already the 'fear of the newbie'.
However, if the client is married but still has no children, it is preferable to negotiate insurance at all risk, as long as his economic situation allows it, of course.
For their part, marriages with children are considered by the insurers as the public with the lowest accident rate, so the surcharges will be lower.
In this case the best insurance would be one at full risk with deductible (it could be 300 euros), or, when a high level of bonus is available, one extended to third parties from the third year of life of the vehicle.
“They carry out a more relaxed driving and have a greater purchasing power to allow themselves to take on a greater amount of franchise,” says Luis Noguera.
For retirees, it is advisable to have an all-risk insurance with franchise (this being 150 euros), or an extended one to third parties when you have a high level of bonus.
It must be said that car insurance is something important, not only because it covers the driver in case of possible accidents, but also because it represents an important expense, which is why it is essential to properly study the insurance that suits us best according to our personal situation.
