It has only 20.05 percent of the share capital.
There was a lot of speculation about the company's takeover.
There are also options to further increase the financial part at Versatel.
United Internet reported that with this step it wants to accelerate the consolidation of the German DSL (Digital Subscriber Line) market.
On Wednesday they already made the assumptions about entering the business, after the Brendenberg bank increased its stake in the Duesseldorf network operator by 5 percent to 15.1 percent.
In the financial market this means that the financial institution maintains equity securities for a third-party partner.
United Internet already in the previous day involved with almost 10 per cent to the telecommunications company Drillisch.
Drillisch in the capital expansion measure placed 17.4 million of the new shares that have a value of 106.4 million euros.
United Internet bought 5.15 million shares for 31.4 million euros.
In addition, the companies began negotiations on DSL-products marketing cooperation.
“We are strengthening our collaboration,” the United Internet spokesperson said.
The two companies founded an MSP joint venture to acquire competitor Freenet.
On Thursday, United Internet reported that at first, the two companies want to be happy with the ten percent stake in Freenet and do not make use of their right, that is, they involve 18.49 per hundreds of Freenet.
That meant both companies kept all options, especially participation in the Freenet corporation.
Negotiations between United Internet and Freenet on a strategic partnership ended in mid-November.
This “game” with Freenet that will last for many months and is not very understandable is part of the consolidation of the German Telecom market.
At the end of the third quarter Freenet had 2.9 million customers with a mobile phone contract and 1.27 million with a DSL contract or a full contract.
Until now the holding company of United Internet and Drillisch held directly 6.01 percent of the stake in Freenet.
